Data loading and processing 

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# explore subject demographic info
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# load subject info
Subj_info_2020 = read.csv("../RawData/Training/2020/2020LD_subject.tsv", sep = "\t")
Subj_info_2021 = read.csv("../RawData/Training/2021/2021LD_subject.tsv", sep = "\t")

# calculate ages at boost shot
Subj_info_2020 = Subj_info_2020 %>%
  mutate(date_of_boost = as.Date(date_of_boost),
         year_of_birth = as.Date(year_of_birth)) %>%
  mutate(age = round(as.numeric(difftime(date_of_boost, year_of_birth, units = "days") / 365), 1))

Subj_info_2021 = Subj_info_2021 %>%
  mutate(date_of_boost = as.Date(date_of_boost),
         year_of_birth = as.Date(year_of_birth)) %>%
  mutate(age = round(as.numeric(difftime(date_of_boost, year_of_birth, units = "days") / 365), 1))

# two datasets have the same data format, combine them
Subj_info = rbind(Subj_info_2020, Subj_info_2021)

theme_age = theme(panel.border = element_rect(colour = "black", fill = NA, size = 1), 
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),

        axis.text.x = element_text(size = 18, angle = 0, hjust = 0.5, vjust = 1, colour = "black"),
        axis.title.y = element_text(size = 20),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 18))

  geom_jitter(aes(color = biological_sex, fill = biological_sex, shape = race), width = 0.2, alpha = 1.0, size = 3) +

  labs(x = NULL, y = "Age (yrs) at boost") +

Time point data availability of each subject 

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# explore time point data
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
# read time point data
Specimen_2020 = read.csv("../RawData/Training/2020/2020LD_specimen.tsv", sep = "\t")
Specimen_2020$dataset = "2020_dataset"
Specimen_2021 = read.csv("../RawData/Training/2021/2021LD_specimen.tsv", sep = "\t")
Specimen_2021$dataset = "2021_dataset"

# two datasets have the same data format, combine them
Specimen_info = rbind(Specimen_2020, Specimen_2021)

Specimen_info$subject_id = paste("PID", Specimen_info$subject_id, sep = "_")
Specimen_info$visit = paste("v", Specimen_info$visit, sep = "")

# only keep Subject and Status
data_sel = Specimen_info[,c(2,6)]

# convert long to wide format
data_sel = data_sel %>%
  tidyr::pivot_wider(names_from = visit, values_from = visit)

# fill 0/1 if data presents
data_sel$v1 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v1), 1, 0)
data_sel$v2 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v2), 1, 0)
data_sel$v3 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v3), 1, 0)
data_sel$v4 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v4), 1, 0)
data_sel$v5 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v5), 1, 0)
data_sel$v6 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v6), 1, 0)
data_sel$v7 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v7), 1, 0)
data_sel$v8 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v8), 1, 0)
data_sel$v9 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v9), 1, 0)
data_sel$v10 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v10), 1, 0)
data_sel$v11 = ifelse(!is.na(data_sel$v11), 1, 0)
# prepare column info
column_info = tribble(
  ~id,         ~group,      ~name,    ~geom,            ~palette,           ~options,
  "subject_id",      "",       "",       "text",           NA,              list(hjust = 1, width = 5),
  "v1",       "",       "Visit1",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v2",       "",       "Visit2",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v3",       "",       "Visit3",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v4",       "",       "Visit4",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v5",       "",       "Visit5",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v6",       "",       "Visit6",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v7",       "",       "Visit7",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v8",       "",       "Visit8",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(), 
  "v9",       "",       "Visit9",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v10",      "",      "Visit10",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
  "v11",      "",      "Visit11",     "funkyrect",     "palette1",          list(),
)

# plot
funky_heatmap(data_sel, column_info = column_info, scale_column = FALSE, 
              palettes =  list(palette1 = "black"),
              expand = list(xmax = 1), col_annot_angle = 90)
